dc_title_s: South America--west coast, Chile, approaches to Antofagasta (Raster Image)
dc_description_s: Prepared and published by the Defense Mapping Agency Hydrographic/Topographic Center. Depths shown by isolines and soundings. Relief shown by contours, hachures, and spot heights. "From Chilean charts to 1982." "Copyright restrictions of the country of origin continue to exist." "Soundings in meters." Includes compilation diagram and tidal information. Map No.22222 This map is part of a collection of scanned and georeferenced nautical charts produced by the National Geospatial-Intelligence Agency (NGA). United States. Defense Mapping Agency. (1990). South America--west coast, Chile, approaches to Antofagasta (Raster Image). LandInfo. Available at: https://purl.stanford.edu/sg624mp2662 This layer is presented in the WGS84 coordinate system for web display purposes. Downloadable data are provided in native coordinate system or projection.
